      • subscribe

        EventService.EventMonitor subscribe(akka.actor.ActorRef subscriber,
                                    boolean postLastEvents,
                                    java.lang.String... prefixes)
        Subscribes an actor to telemetry events matching the given prefixes Each prefix may be followed by a '*' wildcard to subscribe to all matching events.
        Parameters:
        subscriber - an actor to receive StatusEvent messages
        postLastEvents - if true, the subscriber receives the last known values of any subscribed events
        prefixes - one or more prefixes of events, may include wildcard

      • subscribe

        EventService.EventMonitor subscribe(IBlockingTelemetryService.TelemetryHandler callback,
                                    boolean postLastEvents,
                                    java.lang.String... prefixes)
        Subscribes a callback function to telemetry events matching the given prefixes Each prefix may be followed by a '*' wildcard to subscribe to all matching events.
        Parameters:
        callback - an callback which will be called with StatusEvent objects (in another thread)
        postLastEvents - if true, the subscriber receives the last known values of any subscribed events
        prefixes - one or more prefixes of events, may include wildcard

      • getTelemetryService

        static IBlockingTelemetryService getTelemetryService(java.lang.String name,
                                                     akka.actor.ActorRefFactory sys,
                                                     akka.util.Timeout timeout)
        Looks up the Redis instance for the Telemetry Service with the Location Service and then returns an TelemetryService instance using it.

        Note: Applications using the Location Service should call LocationService.initialize() once before accessing any Akka or Location Service methods.

        Parameters:
        name - name used to register the Redis instance with the Location Service (default: "Telemetry Service")
        sys - required Akka environment
        timeout - amount of time to wait looking up name with the location service before giving up with an error
        Returns:
        a future ITelemetryService instance

      • getTelemetryService

                                                     int port,
                                                     akka.actor.ActorRefFactory sys,
                                                     akka.util.Timeout timeout)
        Returns an ITelemetryService instance using the Redis instance at the given host and port
        Parameters:
        host - the Redis host name or IP address
        port - the Redis port
        Returns:
        a new ITelemetryService instance
